">has enjoined upon His disciples that they </div><div class="t m1a0 x92 h4 y14e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">co-operate with Him in His work.&quot;—Ellen </div><div class="t m80c x15 h4 y5f8 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">G. White, </div><div class="t m2d3 x83 h30 yf8 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Review and Herald, </div><div class="t m22a x43 h4 yf8 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Nov. 30, </div><div class="t m1abf x92 h4 y1072 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1886. </div><div class="t me15 x5d h5 y34a ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ&apos;s Mission Among Men </div><div class="t m988 x26 h2d y22e8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m101d x61 h2d y501 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What taunt of the Pharisees </div><div class="t m107a x15 h2d yb5 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">brought forth the three parables in </div><div class="t ma08 x15 h2d y613 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">this lesson? Luke 15:1, 2. </div><div class="t m1ac x16 h4 y91 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.—&quot;The Pharisees had only scorn </div><div class="t m22e x92 h4 y4e7 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and condemnation for them [sinners] ; but </div><div class="t m23a x15 h4 y31d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ greeted them as children of God, </div><div class="t m340 x92 h4 yf18 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">estranged indeed from the Father&apos;s house, </div><div class="t m12ea x15 h4 y10 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">but not forgotten by the Father&apos;s heart. </div><div class="t m2af x92 h4 y9d1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">And their very misery and sin made them </div><div class="t m110 x15 h4 y33d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">only the more the objects of His compas-</div><div class="t m5e8 x92 h4 y420 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sion. The farther they had wandered from </div><div class="t m221 x15 h4 y422 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Him, the more earnest the longing and the </div><div class="t ma50 x15 h4 y5c4 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">greater the sacrifice for their rescue.&quot;—</div><div class="t m274 x15 h30 y6b0 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ&